genresAdvancedInfo.name: melbourne hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Melbourne hip hop is a subgenre of hip hop that originated in Melbourne, Australia. The music is characterized by its laid-back and chilled-out vibe, with smooth beats and introspective lyrics that revolve around personal experiences, relationships, and social issues. The music often incorporates elements of jazz, funk, and soul, and is known for its innovative and experimental approach to hip hop.
